<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Twelve-year-old Helen Keller lived in a prison of silence and darkness. Born deaf, blind, and mute, with no way to express herself or comprehend those<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Twelve-year-old Helen Keller lived in a prison of silence and darkness. Born deaf, blind, and mute, with no way to express herself or comprehend those around her, she flew into primal rages against anyone who tried to help her, fighting tooth and nail with a strength born of furious, unknowing desperation<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
