<div id="review_3672403583" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3672403583" />
    <a title="Toria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27369602-toria"><img alt="Toria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1616719071p2/27369602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3672403583?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Toria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Toria" href="/user/show/27369602-toria">Toria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3672403583" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5521013221187817890">I wanted something short to nibble on and because I knew a little about Hellen Keller and Annie Sullivan I decided to pick it up. I wasn&apos;t prepared for this to be so intense. Even if it&apos;s a play it&apos;s has such an intense force to it and it&apos;s very moving. I would love to see this play someday. Have started picking up plays recently but haven&apos;t really watched them in real life</span>
